  "texts": [
    "The resulting approximation is a tractable Gaussian density given by g (θ) enkf,t (x t |y 0:t, x1:N t) = p (θ) enkf,t (x t |y 0:t-1, x1:N t)g (θ) t (y t |x t) g (θ) enkf,t (y t |y 0:t-1, x1:N t).",
    "Hence, the denominator g",
    "enkf,t t |y 0:t-1, x1:N t) can be computed analytically using Algorithm 3, for a suitable choice of H and R, deduced from the example specific g (θ)",
    "Parameter (and state) filtering may then proceed via the NEnKF (Algorithm 6) at the expense of inferential accuracy, due to the additional error induced by g (θ)",
    "Naturally, inferential accuracy can be maintained at the expense of computational cost, by eschewing the EnKF in favour of the particle filter with target p (θ) t (x t |y 0:t) given by (3)."
